\title{weak algebra [homomorphisms](jms-00C8) and [successor algebra homomorphisms](jms-00CA) are interchangeable}
\taxon{corollary}
\date{2023-11-05}
\author{jonmsterling}
\import{base-macros}
\import{jms-00CD}
\import{jms-00C6}
\import{jms-00C9}

\let\T{#{T}}
\let\TT{#{\mathbb{T}}}
\let\C{#{\mathcal{C}}}
\let\X{#{X}}
\let\I{#{I}}

\p{Let \TT be a monad on a category \C and let \I be an invertible [\em{weak} algebra](jms-00C8) for \TT; let \X be an arbitrary [successor algebra](jms-00C9). Then a morphism \Mor{j}{\I}{\X} in \C tracks a weak algebra homomorphism \Mor{j}{I}{s\cdot X} if and only if it tracks a [successor algebra homomorphism](jms-00CA) \Mor{j}{\ToMonadAlg{\I}}{\X}, where \ToMonadAlg{\I} is the [induced successor algebra](jms-00CN) of \I and #{s\cdot\X} is the [successor restriction](jms-00CC) of \X.}

\proof{
  \p{This follows from the following two lemmas:}
  \ol{
    \li{[[jms-00CR]];}
    \li{[[jms-00D9]].}
  }
}
